// useDiagramUpdateQueue
// Batches and debounces diagram updates so only the latest update per diagram is applied when the timer fires.

Default debounce is 100ms. Multiple updates to the same diagram ID within the window are collapsed
into one — only the last content/timestamp wins.

FUNCTION useDiagramUpdateQueue(updateDiagram, options) -> { queueUpdate, flushNow }  EXPORT
  Maintains an in-memory map of pending updates keyed by diagram ID.
  On unmount, cancels any pending debounce timer (pending updates are discarded).

---

FUNCTION flush()
  Applies all pending updates by calling the updateDiagram callback for each entry, then clears the map.

---

FUNCTION queueUpdate(id, content, lastModified)
  Adds or replaces the pending update for the given diagram ID.
  Resets the debounce timer; flush is called when the timer expires.

---

FUNCTION flushNow()
  Cancels the debounce timer and calls flush immediately.
